The paper discusses structured prediction in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) since the paper specifically applies the proposed technique to scene understanding in computer vision. Additionally, the paper mentions incorporating feature computation trade-offs, which suggests a focus on optimization and efficiency, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) also possible sub-categories.
